						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up near the village <hi rend="italic">chāvaḍi.</hi></p>						

						<p>Sivāji, 1679 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1601, Siddhārthi, Śrāvaṇa śu. 4, corresponding to 1679 A.D., July 31 (not verifiable).</p>						

						<p>It records the grant of the privileges of <hi rend="italic">Gauḍike</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Śānabōvike</hi> to Saṁgappa. It mentions the temples of Haṇamanta and Saṅkaraliṅga. The record is damaged and indifferently engraved. </p>						

						</summary>
